<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Genomics on Rachid Youven Zeghlache</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/tags/genomics/</link><description>Recent content in Genomics on Rachid Youven Zeghlache</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 01 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://youvenzful.github.io/tags/genomics/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>GenomeInterp</title><link>https://youvenzful.github.io/projects/genomeinterp/</link><pubDate>Sat, 01 Jun 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://youvenzful.github.io/projects/genomeinterp/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="overview">Overview&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>GenomeInterp&lt;/strong> is a PyTorch framework for training and interpreting neural networks that predict the regulatory effects of genomic variants.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="features">Features&lt;/h2>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Attention-based model architecture for sequence-to-function mapping&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Built-in saliency map and SHAP-based explanation tools&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Benchmarked on the ENCODE and GTEx datasets&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2 id="installation">Installation&lt;/h2>
